HELP = "Possible commands: \n\t'move' or 'm' followed by the start and end locations \n\t'place' or 'p' followed by the location and orientation of the wall \n\t'jump' or 'j' followed by the start and end locations and the direction of the jump \n\t'help' followed by action (move, place, jump) for more information on the action (e.g. 'help move') \n\t'q' to quit"
HELP_MOVE = "The move action is used to move a pawn to an adjacent cell. The start and end locations as well as the direction of movement must be provided. \nThe start and end locations should be in the format 'a1' or 'i9'. \nExample: 'move up a1 a2'"
HELP_PLACE =  "The place action is used to place a wall on the board. The location and orientation of the wall must be provided. \nWalls can be placed horizontally or vertically \nVertical walls are placed to the lefft of the location and extend downards. \nHorizontal walls are placed above the location and extend to the right. \nWalls are two cells long and can not overlap. \nExample: 'place a1 h'"
